&lt;p&gt;Bittrex, a Seattle-based cryptocurrency exchange,&amp;nbsp;is hiring a Product Owner over crypto wallets. Founded by three cybersecurity engineers in 2014,&amp;nbsp;we build our products with security first, offering&amp;nbsp;access to over 100 cryptocurrencies in the United States along with lightning-fast trade execution and dependable digital wallets.&amp;nbsp;We believe in the potential of blockchain and its ability to provide game-changing solutions, and we’re looking for talented and passionate individuals to join our exceptional team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Product Owner with strong technical skills that understands and has experience with 3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; party API integrations. As a Product Owner you will be working alongside talented developers, designers, and our Crypto Wallets Product Manager to expand blockchain project integrations (Coins &amp;amp; Tokens) into our Bittrex crypto wallet infrastructure. Crypto Wallets are a critical and highly impactful area to our organization and can positively impact both our internal teams and our external customer experience. You will be the voice of the customer, and imperative in eliminating customer pain points. You will be seen as a subject matter expert who can answer engineering team questions and communicate effectively with support teams. This role is an ideal opportunity for someone who is excited to get their hands dirty, is detail oriented and skilled at executing 3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; party integrations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the bridge between product and development teams - Translate the understanding of the product manager’s vision and what each product area is designed to do for its users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate the Product Managers’ strategies and business requirements into well-defined product requirements including features, user stories, and acceptance test criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to explain the “how” and “why” behind all the user stories and other tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the market and customer needs to be useful in translating the strategic plan into the right execution steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the team daily standup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, edit, maintain the team backlog by working closely with PM, Dev, and support teams to ensure technology needs and business needs are adequately represented in priority order.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and own the Product backlog grooming meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the engineering team in establishing normalized estimation practices and work towards an accurate understanding of team capacity and velocity so that delivery estimates are practical.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sprint Planning- Coordinate dependencies with other Product Owners. Communicate story level detail and priorities to the team and ensure the team aligns and agrees on a final sprint plan. Ensure team focus is divided adequately between strategic items, maintenance/bugs, and discretionary needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Answer dev questions about user stories or tasks throughout the sprint.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accept &amp;amp; Validate Stories- work with team to agree on definition of done. Validate stories to ensure they meet acceptance criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Backlog Priority- Work outside the normal scrum meetings with the business stakeholders/ Product Mangers to continually review and update the product backlog priority&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the team end of sprint demos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the team sprint retrospective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be part of the first line of defense for Production Support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make decisions- the product owner role is a decision-making role. You will be responsible and accountable for the product and making decisions daily. These decisions range from what items to include in the product backlog, how to triage production issues, how to prioritize requests, and how to best communicate the same to the engineering and support teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience as a Product Owner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in software development planning, resource management, and product delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent at breaking down business requirements into user stories and acceptance criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organized and thorough in following best practices for stand ups and sprint planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience integrating with third party platforms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at communicating with business support teams and development teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well versed in risk analysis and making complex business/risk trade-off recommendations and decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of Agile SDLC and Change Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to thrive in a fast-paced startup environment where you sometimes need to wear multiple hats and step outside your box of responsibilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written, verbal, and storytelling communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to collect and analyze information, solve complex problems rationally, and make decisions on time for enhanced productivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a Product Owner over API integrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cryptocurrencies, blockchain technology, and digital assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Azure Dev Ops for user story and content management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with financial technology, investment banking, trading, or similar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience integrating 3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; party vendors and managing the lifecycle of API products.&lt;/li&gt;
